The paper focuses on designing automatic programs to optimize the structure of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) for a specific task, which falls under the category of neural network optimization (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the use of genetic programming, which is a machine learning technique (cs.LG). The optimization is done for image classification tasks, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of evolutionary algorithms, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the use of optimization techniques to reduce computational costs, which is related to control systems (cs.SY).
